President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. had a conversation with President Emmanuel Macron of France, Chancellor Olaf Scholz of Germany, Prime Minister Mario Draghi of Italy, and Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom. They expressed their commitment to increasing pressure on Russia for its aggressive actions in Ukraine and providing Ukraine with security assistance to defend itself. The leaders also discussed their efforts to provide humanitarian aid to those affected by the violence and emphasized the need for humanitarian access to civilians in Mariupol. Additionally, they talked about supporting stable energy markets amidst disruptions caused by sanctions.